content.description:
This is a different route, it really a boulder problem with a shity landing, start by climbing on the ledge about 6' high. Climb between the crack on the left and the corner on the right. The limestone features are amazing and solid.

This route is on the back of the bouldering wall at the end, farthest from the main face, it follows the "glued" on limestone featured.
This route can take some cam(s) around your waist when you on the first ledge. Really look for small cam or nut placements around mid face.

The bouldering wall is this spine of rock (shale) that protrudes from the ground. It ranges in height from 8-25 feet, and should remain a bouldering wall with no bolts on it. The shale is mostly sharp and not that enjoyable to climb. There are some sections on the spine that have limestone features stuck to the shale, this make for interesting climbing.
